<p><strong>Skills</strong> Intimidation +2, Medicine +4, Survival +4</p>

<p><strong>Senses</strong> darkvision 60 ft.</p>

<p><strong>Languages</strong> Common, Orc</p>

<p><strong>Challenge</strong> 2 (450 XP)</p>

<p><strong><em>Source.</em></strong> Voloâ€™s Guide to Monsters, p. 183</p>

<p><strong><em>Aggressive.</em></strong> As a bonus action, the orc can move up to its speed toward a hostile creature that it can see.</p>

<p><strong><em>Spellcasting.</em></strong> The orc is a 5th-level spellcaster. Its spellcasting ability is Wisdom (spell save DC 12, +4 to hit with spell attacks). The orc has the following cleric spells prepared:</p>

<p>Cantrips (at will): guidance, mending, resistance, thaumaturgy</p>

<p>1st level (4 slots): bane, cure wounds, guiding bolt</p>

<p>2nd level (3 slots): augury, warding bond</p>

<p>3rd level (2 slots): bestow curse, create food and water</p>

<p><strong>Actions</strong></p>

<p><strong><em>Multiattack.</em></strong> The orc makes two claw attacks, or four claw attacks if it has fewer than half of its hit points remaining.</p>

<p><strong><em>Claw.</em></strong> Melee Weapon Attack: +4 to hit, reach 5 ft., one target. Hit: 6 (1d8+2) slashing damage.</p>

